                                                                "author":  "Choascraft",
                                                                "title":  "Infected Zombie Manual",
                                                                "pages":  [
                                                                              "Infected Zombie Manual\n\nA Choascraft guide for infected zombie variants, scavenged drops, rare gear, and the Sunking Captain legend.",
                                                                              "The Infection\n\nInfected zombies are not one creature. Walkers, runners, spitters, scavengers, impalers, and crushers all feed this loot table.",
                                                                              "Lore\n\nThe infection leaves tools, bones, sea things, and old treasures tangled in its wake. Every corpse is a pocket of the world it crossed.",
                                                                              "Variants\n\nWalkers are the baseline. Runners close distance. Spitters fight at range. Impalers and crushers are heavier threats.",
                                                                              "Common Drops\n\nThe table can roll survival scraps: rotten flesh, bones, string, coal, flint, leather, feathers, arrows, food, sticks, kelp, fish, and more.",
                                                                              "Treasure Drops\n\nRare rolls include emeralds, diamonds, echo shards, saddles, name tags, golden apples, tridents, netherite materials, and other loot.",
                                                                              "Sunking Captain Gear\n\nA rare player-kill roll can drop Sunking Captain armor pieces or the Sunking Captain Sword.",
                                                                              "Sunking Lore\n\nCaptain Morvane Tideborn went below the black water in armor made for crushing depth. The infection remembers him badly.",
                                                                              "Gear Uses\n\nSunking Captain gear is special loot, not normal crafted gear. Treat each piece as a relic from the trench wars.",
                                                                              "Ocean Link\n\nThe infected table carries ocean items because the rot moved through drowned ships, reefs, trenches, and zombie sea beasts.",
                                                                              "Hunter Note\n\nIf you want relics, bring Looting and patience. If you want to live, bring distance."
